metadata.name: High Gas #1/9
metadata.description:
It was midnight and the streets were silent. At the local gas station, a man pulled up in his car. He was frustrated, not only because the gas prices were high, but because he felt helpless. He had no other choice but to pay the outrageous prices. 

After filling up his tank, the man stepped out of his car and walked to the front of the station. He looked back at his car, then pulled out a lighter from his pocket. He flicked the lighter open and threw it onto the car, setting it aflame. 

The man watched as the flames engulfed his car, the light casting an orange glow across the otherwise dark night. He knew this was the only way to make a statement and get his message across. 

The man stood there until the fire was extinguished, then walked away in the darkness, his silent protest now complete.
